  "title": "Sales Admin Coordinator #81364",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: F&B Vending Service</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Sales Coordinator</strong></li><li>Working Location: Bukit Merah (Walk distance from MRT)</li><li>Working Hours: Monday – Friday (8.45am – 5.30pm), Alternate Saturday (8.45am – 12.45pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic Salary (Yearly increment) + Variable Bonus (Profit Sharing)</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Manage sales coordination, delivery arrangements, and machine deployment to ensure smooth day-to-day operations.</li><li>Develop and sustain positive, long-term relationships with customers.</li><li>Liaise confidently with the Director, Operations Manager, and clients to support business needs and project execution.</li><li>Review and interpret sales data to identify trends, generate insights, and recommend improvements.</li><li>Collaborate closely with drivers, technicians, and administrative staff to maintain seamless operations.</li><li>Source and pursue new leads and growth opportunities to expand market coverage.</li><li>Handle contracts, agreements, and tender documents on an ad-hoc basis, including proofreading and ensuring accuracy.</li><li>Perform other related duties as assigned by management.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum GCE ‘O’ Level or above.</li><li>Detail-oriented with strong interpersonal, customer service, and communication abilities.</li><li>Highly proficient with Microsoft Office, especially Excel for numerical data handling and reporting.</li><li>With proofreading skills for contracts, agreements and experience in handling tender documents will be added advantage</li><li>Adaptable, and must be able to work independently in a fast-paced environment to prevent backlogs for smooth operations.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#81364 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
